---
// FontShowcase.astro - Component to demonstrate the Emerald Sanctuary font system
---

<div class="font-showcase max-w-4xl mx-auto p-8 space-y-12">
  <!-- Hero/Display Font - Bricolage Grotesque -->
  <section class="space-y-4">
    <h1
      class="hero-title text-transparent"
      style="font-family: 'Bricolage Grotesque', ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif; background-image: linear-gradient(135deg, hsl(142, 18%, 38%) 0%, hsl(156, 50%, 45%) 50%, hsl(142, 12%, 58%) 100%); background-clip: text; -webkit-background-clip: text; -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;"
    >
      Emerald Sanctuary
    </h1>
    <p
      class="hero-subtitle text-muted-foreground"
      style="font-family: 'Bricolage Grotesque', ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;"
    >
      Calm-but-quirky curves echo natural forms
    </p>
    <div class="text-sm text-muted-foreground font-body">
      Font: Bricolage Grotesque • Use: Logo & hero headlines
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Heading Font - Clash Grotesk -->
  <section class="space-y-4">
    <h2
      class="section-heading text-foreground"
      style="font-family: 'Clash Grotesk', ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif; font-size: 2.5rem; font-weight: 600; line-height: 1.2;"
    >
      Confident Typography
    </h2>
    <h3
      class="subsection-heading text-foreground"
      style="font-family: 'Clash Grotesk', ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif; font-size: 1.875rem; font-weight: 600; line-height: 1.3;"
    >
      Modern web typography that pops
    </h3>
    <h4
      class="card-heading text-foreground"
      style="font-family: 'Clash Grotesk', ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif; font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 600; line-height: 1.4;"
    >
      Tech-meets-editorial aesthetic
    </h4>
    <div class="text-sm text-muted-foreground font-body">
      Font: Clash Grotesk • Use: Section headings
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Body Font - Inter Variable -->
  <section class="space-y-4">
    <div
      class="body-large text-foreground"
      style="font-family: 'Inter Variable', ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif; font-size: 1.25rem; line-height: 1.6;"
    >
      This is large body text using Inter Variable. The font's optical sizing automatically adjusts
      for optimal readability at this size, while its neutral character lets emerald accents
      breathe.
    </div>
    <div
      class="body-regular text-foreground"
      style="font-family: 'Inter Variable', ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif; font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.7;"
    >
      This is regular body text that maintains excellent readability across all viewports. Inter's
      comprehensive character set and careful spacing make it perfect for long-form content and
      technical documentation.
    </div>
    <div
      class="body-small text-muted-foreground"
      style="font-family: 'Inter Variable', ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif; font-size: 0.875rem; line-height: 1.6;"
    >
      Small body text remains crisp and readable even at reduced sizes, thanks to Inter's thoughtful
      design and variable font technology.
    </div>
    <div class="text-sm text-muted-foreground font-body">
      Font: Inter Variable • Use: Body text & navigation
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Code/Stats Font - Geist Mono -->
  <section class="space-y-4">
    <div
      class="stats-block text-primary"
      style="font-family: 'Geist Mono', ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, monospace; font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: -0.025em;"
    >
      Portfolio Statistics
    </div>
    <div
      class="caption text-muted-foreground"
      style="font-family: 'Geist Mono', ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, monospace; font-size: 0.875rem; line-height: 1.6;"
    >
      Geist Mono is used for code snippets and stat blocks, providing a modern, clean monospace
      experience perfect for technical content.
    </div>
    <div
      class="metadata text-muted-foreground"
      style="font-family: 'Geist Mono', ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, monospace; font-size: 0.75rem; letter-spacing: 0.1em; text-transform: uppercase;"
    >
      Code Snippets • Stat Blocks • Technical Data
    </div>
    <div class="text-sm text-muted-foreground font-body">
      Font: Geist Mono • Use: Code snippets / stat blocks
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Code Font - Geist Mono -->
  <section class="space-y-4">
    <div
      class="text-lg font-heading text-foreground"
      style="font-family: 'Clash Grotesk', ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;"
    >
      Code Examples
    </div>
    <div class="space-y-2">
      <p
        class="body-regular text-foreground"
        style="font-family: 'Inter Variable', ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;"
      >
        Inline code like <code
          class="code-inline"
          style="font-family: 'Geist Mono', ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, monospace; background: hsl(var(--secondary)); padding: 0.125rem 0.25rem; border-radius: 0.25rem;"
          >const sanctuary = 'emerald'</code
        > integrates seamlessly with body text.
      </p>
      <pre
        class="code-block bg-secondary text-secondary-foreground p-4 rounded-lg overflow-x-auto"
        style="font-family: 'Geist Mono', ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, monospace;"><code>{`// Geist Mono for code blocks
function createSanctuary() {
  return {
    theme: 'emerald',
    typography: 'modern',
    feel: 'mystical'
  };
}`}</code></pre>
    </div>
    <div class="text-sm text-muted-foreground font-body">
      Font: Geist Mono • Use: Code snippets and technical content
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Flourish Font - Fraunces -->
  <section class="space-y-6">
    <div
      class="pull-quote text-primary"
      style="font-family: 'Fraunces', ui-serif, Georgia, serif; font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 400; line-height: 1.4; font-style: italic;"
    >
      "Design is not just what it looks like and feels like. Design is how it works."
    </div>
    <div class="flex items-center gap-8">
      <div
        class="big-number text-accent"
        style="font-family: 'Fraunces', ui-serif, Georgia, serif; font-size: 4rem; font-weight: 900; line-height: 0.9;"
      >
        42
      </div>
      <div
        class="elegant-accent text-foreground"
        style="font-family: 'Fraunces', ui-serif, Georgia, serif; font-size: 1.125rem; font-weight: 400; line-height: 1.5;"
      >
        Projects completed with botanical-inspired typography
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="text-sm text-muted-foreground font-body">
      Font: Fraunces Variable • Use: Pull quotes & special numerals
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Font Hierarchy Demonstration -->
  <section class="content-section space-y-6 p-6 bg-card rounded-lg border">
    <h2
      style="font-family: 'Clash Grotesk', ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif; font-size: 2rem; font-weight: 600;"
    >
      Complete Font Hierarchy
    </h2>
    <h3
      style="font-family: 'Clash Grotesk', ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif; font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 600;"
    >
      This section demonstrates font pairing
    </h3>

    <p
      style="font-family: 'Inter Variable', ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif; line-height: 1.7;"
    >
      This paragraph uses the default body font (Inter Variable) and demonstrates how all fonts work
      together harmoniously. The <code
        style="font-family: 'Geist Mono', ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, monospace; background: hsl(var(--secondary)); padding: 0.125rem 0.25rem; border-radius: 0.25rem;"
        >code snippets</code
      > use Geist Mono, while headings above use Clash Grotesk.
    </p>

    <blockquote
      class="border-l-4 border-primary pl-4"
      style="font-family: 'Fraunces', ui-serif, Georgia, serif; font-style: italic; font-size: 1.125rem; line-height: 1.6;"
    >
      Blockquotes use the elegant Fraunces font to add sophistication and visual interest to quoted
      content.
    </blockquote>

    <div
      class="caption"
      style="font-family: 'Inter Variable', ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif; font-size: 0.875rem; color: hsl(var(--muted-foreground));"
    >
      This caption now uses Inter Variable as the body font, maintaining consistency with the
      hierarchy.
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Responsive Examples -->
  <section class="space-y-4">
    <h2
      class="section-heading text-foreground"
      style="font-family: 'Clash Grotesk', ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif; font-size: 2rem; font-weight: 600;"
    >
      Responsive Typography
    </h2>
    <p
      class="body-regular text-muted-foreground"
      style="font-family: 'Inter Variable', ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif; line-height: 1.7;"
    >
      All fonts scale appropriately across different screen sizes, maintaining readability and
      visual hierarchy from mobile to desktop.
    </p>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 text-sm">
      <div class="p-4 bg-secondary rounded">
        <div
          class="font-semibold mb-2"
          style="font-family: 'Clash Grotesk', ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;"
        >
          Mobile
        </div>
        <div style="font-family: 'Inter Variable', ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;">
          Optimized scaling for touch devices
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="p-4 bg-secondary rounded">
        <div
          class="font-semibold mb-2"
          style="font-family: 'Clash Grotesk', ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;"
        >
          Tablet
        </div>
        <div style="font-family: 'Inter Variable', ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;">
          Balanced proportions for medium screens
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="p-4 bg-secondary rounded">
        <div
          class="font-semibold mb-2"
          style="font-family: 'Clash Grotesk', ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;"
        >
          Desktop
        </div>
        <div style="font-family: 'Inter Variable', ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;">
          Full typographic expression
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Font Loading Debug Section -->
  <section class="space-y-4 p-4 bg-muted rounded-lg">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-foreground">Font Loading Debug</h3>
    <div class="space-y-2 text-sm">
      <div style="font-family: 'Bricolage Grotesque', sans-serif;">Bricolage Grotesque Test</div>
      <div style="font-family: 'Clash Grotesk', sans-serif;">Clash Grotesk Test</div>
      <div style="font-family: 'Inter Variable', sans-serif;">Inter Variable Test</div>
      <div style="font-family: 'Geist Mono', monospace;">Geist Mono Test</div>
      <div style="font-family: 'Fraunces', serif; font-weight: 400;">Fraunces Regular Test</div>
      <div style="font-family: 'Fraunces', serif; font-weight: 700;">Fraunces Bold Test</div>
      <div style="font-family: 'Fraunces', serif; font-style: italic;">Fraunces Italic Test</div>
    </div>
  </section>
</div>

<style>
  /* Additional showcase-specific styling */
  .font-showcase {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, hsl(var(--background)) 0%, hsl(var(--muted)) 100%);
    border-radius: 1rem;
  }

  /* Ensure proper font loading */
  .hero-title {
    font-display: swap;
  }
</style>
